omplete because carbon source and energy input are omitted. Despite that, the overall pathway is plausible if interpreted as a shorthand for atmospheric HCN supply.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_002\",\n        \"rxn_005\",\n        \"rxn_007\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Rewrite HCN generation to include an explicit carbon source and energy input\",\n        \"Include Cu sulfide photoredox mediation in the cyanosulfidic steps\",\n        \"Disaggregate the dark/light sequence for closer match to Patel et al.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.62,\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.82\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.8,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.88,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.83,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.9,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.84,\n      \"feedback\": \"This pathway is coherent if rxn_002 is treated as shorthand for atmospheric HCN generation rather than a literal stoichiometric reaction. The core Strecker-to-hydrolysis sequence is strong and literature-supported. The main deficiency remains that the network does not explain the source of isobutyraldehyde.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_002\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Correct the HCN formation stoichiometry and include a carbon source\",\n        \"Add environmental context for atmospheric production and rainout of HCN\",\n        \"Address precursor sourcing for isobutyraldehyde\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.62,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.88,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.82\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.81,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.89,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.85,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.9,\n      \"overall_confidence\